## 🔧 Running the Server

The project uses **Daphne** as the ASGI server, which supports Django Channels and WebSockets.

Run the backend from the project root:

```bash
# Runs the Django ASGI application on port 8000 using Daphne.
daphne -p 8000 robotat_web.asgi:application
```

> 📌 Replace `robotat_web` with the name of the root project module that contains `asgi.py`.

By default, the server will be available at:

```text
http://127.0.0.1:8000/
```

