## 🌐 WebSocket Routes

| Route       | Description                                                                      |
| ----------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `/ws/mqtt/` | WebSocket channel that receives real-time messages forwarded by the MQTT client. |

Example connection from the frontend using JavaScript:

```javascript
// Creates a WebSocket connection to the MQTT bridge endpoint.
const socket = new WebSocket("ws://127.0.0.1:8000/ws/mqtt/");

// Defines the function that runs every time a WebSocket message is received.
socket.onmessage = (event) => {
  // Converts the received JSON string into a JavaScript object.
  const data = JSON.parse(event.data);

  // Prints the received MQTT message in the browser console.
  console.log("MQTT message received:", data);
};
```

