## 📤 MQTT Publishing Example

```python
# Defines a generic command packet to be published through MQTT.
packet = {
    # Identifies the source of the packet.
    "src": 1,

    # Defines the source packet timestamp or sequence-related field.
    "pts": 5,

    # Defines the target packet timestamp or sequence-related field.
    "ptp": 10,

    # Identifies the packet type or command identifier.
    "pid": 3,

    # Includes a checksum value used to validate the packet integrity.
    "cks": "a1b2c3",

    # Contains the command payload sent to the robot.
    "pld": {
        # Defines the left wheel velocity.
        "v_l": 0.2,

        # Defines the right wheel velocity.
        "v_r": 0.2
    }
}

# Imports the function used to publish command packets through MQTT.
from mqtt_bridge.mqtt_client import publish_command

# Publishes the command packet to the configured MQTT command topic.
publish_command(packet)
```

